snippet.title: Italians rally against probable change in Constitution
snippet.description:
Italians rally against probable change in Constitution
Toegevoegd door PressTV laatste oktober
On Saturday about 30,000 people gathered in Rome for a demonstration called by authoritative jurists, union leaders and journalists to defend Italy's constitution. The initiative was supported by the daily Il Fatto Quotidiano, a newspaper that since its inception opted to be inspired just by the constitution and to not receive any public funds, unlike all other major Italian newspapers. The demonstrators, who had reached Rome from all over Italy, argued that the principles in the constitutional charter must be applied.

snippet.title: Egypt Revolution Over? Final Day of Voting on New Constitution
snippet.description:
Egypt Revolution Over? Final Day of Voting on New Constitution
Toegevoegd door tvnportal laatste januari
PART 2 - Polls have closed in Egypt on the sixth round of voting since the fall of Hosni Mubarak nearly three years ago. The last few days have seen deadly clashes with supporters of the now-banned Muslim Brotherhood, but also a high turnout from those who are keen to elect the head of the army as president. What's next for political Islam in the Arab World's most populous state? And was Tahrir Square, and the first ever election of a civilian president in Egypt a mere hiatus?Video provided by France 24 Producer : France 24
